Benga musician Bernard Odhiambo Okome, known as Odhiambo Tusker yesterday was charged with assault in a Bondo court. He allegedly assaulted Brian Omondi Jura on August 23 at Amoyo market in Kagwa sublocation, Bondo subcounty. Okome pleaded not guilty and was released on Sh20,000 bond and a similar surety. Principal magistrate Moses Obiero said the case will be mentioned on October 4 and the hearing will begin on October 7. Jura s family had earlier protested against lack of police intervention after they reported the assault at Aram police station in Rarieda subcounty. They went to Bondo police station, where they say they were offered assistance.